@@WTailor's Row@@N~
The tailors' row is a prosperous-looking stretch with polished wood frontages and display mannequins in the wider windows. Sample garments hang in the doorways and the sound of cutting shears and the hiss of steam pressing irons carries from the workshops inside. Measurement notices listing current commission times are posted in neat frames beside each shop entrance.

